to appoint KKR=E2=80=99s board of directors.)</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">For taxes, the standard approach is more complicated. It is called an =
=E2=80=9CUp-C=E2=80=9D corporate structure: The founders make their partner=
ship a=C2=A0subsidiary=C2=A0of a new publicly traded corporation; public sh=
areholders get shares in the corporation, but the founders and other partne=
rs keep their ownership units in the partnership. If they ever want to=C2=
=A0<em>sell</em>=C2=A0those units, they can convert them into the public sh=
ares and sell those. Each partnership unit is convertible into one public s=
hare.</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Normally the conversion is taxable: =
When the partners convert their units into shares, they pay tax on the fair=
